Textron Inc unit BellHelicopter Textron Inc said it and two United Auto Workersunion locals agreed to a new three-year contract, ending athree week strike.    It said production and maintenance members of Local 218 hadbeen on strike for three weeks while clerical members of Local317 had been on strike for a week. A total of 4,000 people wereout on strike.    A company spokesman said the strike was based on adisagreement over the method of future pay rises.    The spokesman said the company's original offer was basedon lump sum payments over three years at six pct in the firstyear, four pct in the second year and three pct in the third.    He said management and the unions later agreed to a systemthat combined general pay increases with lump sum payments overthe life of the contract. Reuter&#3;